In the needs tab the bars on the left are not the only things you have to worry about. The individual mood things which are written on the right are whats actually affecting your colonists moods.

Gura! I don't know if you even read these comments or not, but if you ever do get permission from Cover Corp to play a modded game of RimWorld, I've got a few mods to suggest you play. HAR (Humanoid Alien Races, many of the race mods need this.)
The Moyo (Atlantian-like fish folk.)
The Rabbie (Korean mod, no official translation)
Garam Race Addon/Advanced Apparel (Also Korean, has many Sub mods that add many races. Incompatible with HAR, so some of them have Garam and HAR versions.)
Alpha Biomes/Animals
Dubs... (Just look for DubsMintMenus and grab EVERYTHING by the author.)
Vanilla Expanded (Much like Dubs... it's got a lot.)
VGP Vegetable Garden (Again, got a lot...)
Combat Extended (Incompatible with A LOT of mods, causes a lot of splitting in the community because the dev of CE refuses to collaborate with other mod devs.)

There are A LOT of other good mods, but those really are the big ones that I'd recommend.

text:
Okay Gura, you probably won't read this but here's some tips:

- To improve mood, give each pawn their own bedroom. 3x5 is enough. Big and beautiful rooms are also good. Drugs can also improve mood, consider researching Beer Brewing. It also sells for a good price.
- Prisons don't need to be that big, though the better the prison, the easier it is to recruit prisoners. Put a chess table inside to improve the prisoner's mood so they don't go berserk.
- You should always have at least one Doctor and Warden jobs at highest priority. On your Health tab you can set the doctor to self-tending as well.
- The fired generators will shortcircuit in the rain. Build a roof over them.
- You can have multiple farms at once. If possible, build them on rich soil, which are darker patches of dirt. Rice grows even faster on it.
- Consider planting potato, corn and cotton.
- Check if your cooler is set to freeze things below 0, or your food will keep spoiling.
- Build a hospital, and a medicine storage inside of it.
- Build lamps. Pawns move and work slower in darkness.

Now on the topic of mods:
- I highly recommend that you use at least a few quality of life mods, like Allow Tool (lets you allow all items in the map with a single click), Camera+ (more zoom), RimHUD (better character UI).
- EdB Prepare Carefully allows you to customize your starting colonists, you can choose their skills, appearance, traits, etc. It has a point-buy system to help balancing it.
- Just browse the Steam workshop if you want, there's thousands of cool mods there.

Rimworld is my favorite game and I'm very happy to see you playing it! I hope you enjoy it!

text:
¬†@KazutoSAO47¬† I would highly recommend the new Ideology expansion if you haven't gotten it.  You can range from simple ideologies where little changes, to challenge runs where your ideology punishes you for cutting down trees, to ideologies that make you absurdly powerful with bonuses to crafting and building that boost quality of things that are built or crafted, letting you craft legendary items with out needing an inspiration.  There's extremely good role playing potential in that expansion.

If you go with a cannibal colony, your faction will demand to eat human flesh, and have mood penalties if you don't.  Darkness ideologies get combat bonuses at night, but require special lights and hate going outside while the sun is out.  Tunnelers love the taste of insect meat, and can lay down "fungal gravel" to grow mushrooms (or any crop really) under mountain roofing.  You can have tree worshipping druids, that feel man is a stain on nature's perfection, and so they won't touch trees, they won't mine, and they won't hunt animals.  They also feel letting a machine decide to kill is a horrible evil, so no turrets.  There's a rancher ideology where if you ask anyone to plant crops, they get unhappy because it's not natural for man to eat food grown from the ground, man should eat the animals, and animals should eat the plants that grow naturally, as this is the natural order.  And the list goes on and on.  You get to mix and match these to create your ideology, giving a great ability to customize what you want your colony to believe.

The latest patch added fluid ideologies that build up and develop over time, so you can have a basic ideology with only one major precept (called a meme), build up points from doing things related to your ideology, such as converting people to your ideology, or holding religious events (sacrifices, festivals, parties, etc) then expand the ideology once you've built up enough points.

text:
Hey Gura! It's been a while since I've been able to catch any streams, cause life has been a lot busier lately. Now that I've been able to watch some more these past few days though, I just wanted to say you seem like you're really in your element and doing great lately, and it makes me really happy to see. It's hard not to be proud of you for coming so far these past eleven months. Hopefully your health and sleep have been a little better, but some things won't ever be perfect, and that's okay.

I plan to try and watch a lot more HoloEN in the near future (I've already got a BEEG backlog cause of all the new members!) so I don't know how often I'll be in live streams still. But either way, you and all of HoloMyth will always have a special place in my heart for making this past year much, much better than it otherwise would have been. I love you all, and I'm gonna make SURE I can be there for your anniversaries.

For all the days I won't be here to say it over and over again: try to be kind to yourself, and remember, you're awesome. See you again soon, Little Shark! <3
